Short Senior-Level Version

Memorize this.

“JWT is a stateless authentication mechanism.

After successful login, server generates signed token containing user claims. Client sends token with every request using Authorization header.

Spring Security validates token through JWT filter and sets authentication in SecurityContextHolder.

JWT is mainly useful in scalable and microservice architectures because server doesn’t maintain session state.”
